{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":1000,"text":"Well, I'm involved in other things, besides physics."},{"time":5000,"text":"In fact, mostly now in other things."}]},{"cues":[{"time":7000,"text":"One thing is distant relationships among human languages."},{"time":12000,"text":"And the professional, historical linguists in the U.S."},{"time":16000,"text":"and in Western Europe mostly try to stay away"},{"time":19000,"text":"from any long-distance relationships, big groupings,"},{"time":23000,"text":"groupings that go back a long time,"},{"time":26000,"text":"longer than the familiar families."},{"time":29000,"text":"They don't like that. They think it's crank. I don't think it's crank."},{"time":33000,"text":"And there are some brilliant linguists, mostly Russians,"},{"time":36000,"text":"who are working on that, at Santa Fe Institute and in Moscow,"},{"time":40000,"text":"and I would love to see where that leads."}]},{"cues":[{"time":44000,"text":"Does it really lead to a single ancestor"},{"time":47000,"text":"some 20, 25,000 years ago?"},{"time":50000,"text":"And what if we go back beyond that single ancestor,"},{"time":53000,"text":"when there was presumably a competition among many languages?"},{"time":57000,"text":"How far back does that go? How far back does modern language go?"},{"time":61000,"text":"How many tens of thousands of years does it go back?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":64000,"text":"Chris Anderson: Do you have a hunch or a hope for what the answer to that is?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":67000,"text":"Murray Gell-Mann: Well, I would guess that modern language must be older"},{"time":70000,"text":"than the cave paintings and cave engravings and cave sculptures"},{"time":74000,"text":"and dance steps in the soft clay in the caves in Western Europe,"},{"time":79000,"text":"in the Aurignacian Period some 35,000 years ago, or earlier."},{"time":85000,"text":"I can't believe they did all those things and didn't also have a modern language."},{"time":88000,"text":"So, I would guess that the actual origin goes back at least that far and maybe further."}]},{"cues":[{"time":93000,"text":"But that doesn't mean that all, or many, or most"},{"time":96000,"text":"of today's attested languages couldn't descend perhaps"},{"time":100000,"text":"from one that's much younger than that, like say 20,000 years,"},{"time":104000,"text":"or something of that kind. It's what we call a bottleneck."}]},{"cues":[{"time":108000,"text":"CA: Well, Philip Anderson may have been right."},{"time":109000,"text":"You may just know more about everything than anyone."},{"time":112000,"text":"So, it's been an honor. Thank you Murray Gell-Mann."},{"time":114000,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}